Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel:

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView selection):

```csharp
// Approach A — string ID via query string
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive both in the ViewModel** with a single `IQueryAttributable` implementation:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B: full object passed via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- bindings here -->
</ContentPage>
```

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **Always `await`** `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions.
- **Query strings** serialize to strings; use for simple IDs/flags.
- **`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`** passes live objects without serialization — use when you already have the object in memory.
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called automatically by Shell on the `BindingContext` if it implements `IQueryAttributable`. Both approaches arrive in the same dictionary.
